de.esoco.process.step

Class SubProcessFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.obrel.core.RelatedObject
      • org.obrel.core.SerializableRelatedObject
        • de.esoco.process.ProcessElement
          • de.esoco.process.ProcessFragment
            • de.esoco.process.step.InteractionFragment
              • de.esoco.process.step.SubProcessFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    de.esoco.lib.manage.Initializable, ProcessControlFragment.ProcessExecutionHandler, java.io.Serializable, org.obrel.core.Relatable

    public class SubProcessFragment
extends InteractionFragment
implements ProcessControlFragment.ProcessExecutionHandler
    An interaction fragment that executes a sub-process in the current process and renders it's interactions. This allows to use arbitrary interactive processes inside of other interactions. If the fragment's process consists of multiple steps it needs to handle the transitions between steps by itself because there is no standard process navigation UI for sub-process interactions.

    This fragment set's it's layout to INLINE so that it's interaction parameters will be inserted directly into the parent fragment. If that is not appropriate, e.g. if a single component is required for the parent content, this fragment should be wrapped in another fragment with the corresponding layout.
